definitions.definition: Located indoors , especially at home or at one's office or place of work.

examples: Little by little I pushed the snake into the basket, until finally all of it was in .
The bullet is about five centimetres in .

definitions.definition: Falling or remaining within the bounds of the playing area.
examples: If the tennis ball bounces on the line then it's in .
labels: of the ball or other playing implement
definitions.label_groups: sports , of the ball or other playing implement

examples: I've discovered why the TV wasn't working – the plug wasn't in !
The replies to the questionnaires are now all in .

labels: of the sails of a vessel
definitions.label_groups: nautical , of the sails of a vessel

definitions.definition: Of the tide, at or near its highest level.
examples: You can't get round the headland when the tide's in .

definitions.definition: With privilege or possession; used to denote a holding, possession, or seisin
examples: in by descent; in by purchase; in of the seisin of her husband

definitions.definition: Having familiarity or involvement with somebody.
examples: He is very in with the Joneses.

definitions.definition: Having a favourable position, such as a position of influence or expected gain, in relation to another person.
examples: I need to keep in with the neighbours in case I ever need a favour from them.
I think that bird fancies you. You're in there, mate!

definitions.definition: Having used , consumed , or invested a certain amount.
examples: I'm three drinks in right now.
I was 500 dollars in when the stock crashed.
